Historic ladder created with qualifying path to MC. Initial card pool is cards from: Ixalan, Rivals of Ixalan, Dominaria, Core Set 2019, Guilds of Ravnica, Ravnica Allegiance, War of the Spark, Core Set 2020, and Throne of Eldraine.

Legacy is created (then called Type 1.5). "Type 1.5 tournament decks may be constructed from Magic: The Gathering cards from the Limited (first edition, with black border) series, the Unlimited (second edition), Revised (third edition), Fourth Edition, any Magic: The Gathering expansion (unless expressly disallowed by the head judge prior to the event), and promotional cards released by Wizards of the Coast in magazines or through books." There are no restricted cards. The list of banned cards is the sum of all cards that are either restricted or banned in Vintage or Standard.
Fastbond and Strip Mine are banned. The head judge can't disallow any Magic expansion anymore.
Stroke of Genius, Tolarian Academy, and Windfall are banned. Feldon's Cane is unbanned.
Time Spiral is banned. Candelabra of Tawnos, Copy Artifact, Maze of Ith, Zuran Orb, and Mishra's Workshop are unbanned.

Creation of Standard (then called "Type 2") on January 10, inheriting banned and restricted lists from Vintage. Legal sets are the most recent edition of Magic: the Gathering (Revised at the time), and the two most recent expansions (The Dark and Fallen Empires at the time)
Fourth Edition cards now legal. Revised cards are no longer legal.
Ice Age cards now legal. The Dark cards no longer legal. (?)

Homelands cards now legal. New deck construction rules. Standard (Type 2) can be composed of cards from the most recent edition of Magic The Gathering (Fourth Edition at the time), white border extensions (Chronicles), and all available limited edition expansions (Ice Age, Fallen Empires, and Homelands).
Legendary cards are unrestricted. Zuran Orb is restricted. Channel is banned.
Mind Twist is banned. Black Vise is restricted.
Feldon's Cane and Recall are unrestricted.
Hymn to Tourach and Strip Mine are restricted.
Mirage cards now legal. Fallen Empires cards no longer legal.

All cards on the restricted list are moved to the banned list. New deck construction rules. New editions of the basic set replace old versions and are permitted in Standard play thirty days after the release date of the new edition. New standalone expansions (e.g., Ice Age, Mirage, etc.) replace previous stand-alone expansions and are permitted in Standard play thirty days after the release date of the new edition. Limited-edition expansions are replaced thirty days after the release date of the next limited-edition expansion which has a release date of more than 10 months later than the release date of the outgoing limited-edition expansion.
Fifth Edition cards now legal. Fourth Edition cards no longer legal.

New deck construction rules. Standard decks can be composed of cards from the most recent edition of Magic: The Gathering (then Fifth Edition) and all sets from the two most recent "blocks" of expansions (then Ice Age, Homelands, Alliances, Mirage, Visions, and Weatherlight)
